Package: knockdown
Type: Package
Title: Analysis of high-throughput RNAi gene perturbation screens
Version: 0.1
Date: 2015-12-10
Authors@R: person("Simon", "Dirmeier",
    email = "simon.dirmeier@bsse.ethz.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: knockdown does analysis of large-scale RNAi interference screens
  for pan-pathogenic datasets. The package provides various tools for
  normalisation, plotting and analysis. For single pathogen screens classical
  analyses using hypothesis testing are implemented. For pan-pathogenic
  screens we developed a random effects model that exploits the different
  biological settings the data are derived from. The resulting hit lists can be
  further extended using network diffusion algorithms, such as
  *Markov random walks with restarts*.
